---++ Fourth agenda item
&lt;!-- DESCRIPTION --&gt;
Status of the test stand after kernel upgrade (Andrew, Neha, Tanya)

---+++ Discussion
&lt;!-- describe the discussion that took place --&gt;
   1. !BeStMan/Xrootd restarted without any problems.
   1. Hadoop didn&#39;t start. Andrew has modified ckconfig and send Michael an email proposing to include ckconfig in installation instructions
   1. dcache
After kernel update and reboot we have lost /diskc/local  on one of the pool nodes (gwdca01). After loosing one pool  all the attempts to copy any file to dcache ended up with the following error: &lt;pre class=&quot;screen&quot;&gt;
&quot;Exception in thread &quot;main&quot; org.globus.ftp.exception.ServerException: 
Server refused performing the request. Custom message: Operation 
failed: FTP Door: got response from 
&#39;[&gt;Trash.StoragePoolManager@dCacheDomain:*@dCacheDomain:SrmSpaceManager@srm-
gwdca04Domain:*@srm-gwdca04Domain:*@dCacheDomain]&#39; with error Best 
pool &lt;gwdca02_1&gt; too high : Infinity (error code 1)&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;
It was unclear what was the cause for the problem because the admin interface indicated that  there was lot of free space available. 

It turned out that the &quot;gapPara&quot; parameter that defines min amount of free space for cost calculation is set to 4GB  by default (gwdca02 has 3GB of space). 
It is unclear if this is a configurable parameter  (it is not defined in dCacheSetup) but it could be changed via admin interface (set gap command).  
After the change has been made it was possible to copy files but we are still experience problems with space reservation. 
Dan should try to restore the mount when he comes back from vacation.


